icense suspension, and the Secretary of State shall effectuate the suspension in accordance with state law.(d) Penalties collected under subsection (a)(1) of  this section shall be deposited into the West Virginia Division of Forestry's operating fund to support the administration of the Registry.(e) The Division of Forestry may pursue enforcement actions through the appropriate courts to ensure compliance with this article.NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to establish of a Forest Carbon Registry under the administration of the West Virginia Division of Forestry.Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law and underscoring indicates new language that would be added. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone: